00:14:20,340 --> 00:14:21,705
Do that sound again.

237
00:14:23,710 --> 00:14:25,007
I like that.

238
00:14:28,081 --> 00:14:30,379
<i>And so, on a miraculous play,</i>

239
00:14:30,584 --> 00:14:34,520
<i>the cons end the first half
with the score: 14-all.</i>

240
00:14:39,559 --> 00:14:41,288
Bring it in.

241
00:14:42,029 --> 00:14:45,362
Do you have any idea
who's beating you out there?

242
00:14:45,565 --> 00:14:47,726
This was supposed to be a blowout,

243
00:14:47,934 --> 00:14:51,392
and they're showing you up
in front of the whole nation.

244
00:14:52,472 --> 00:14:54,099
The whole nation!

245
00:14:54,508 --> 00:14:56,703
I like it when he's angry.

246
00:14:58,979 --> 00:15:01,641
- I told you!
- Way to go, baby, way to go.

247
00:15:08,021 --> 00:15:10,888
What in the hell do you think
you're doing out there?

248
00:15:11,091 --> 00:15:12,718
Playing football, sir.

249
00:15:14,428 --> 00:15:16,259
I didn't say nothing about winning.

250
00:15:16,596 --> 00:15:18,826
We're not winning. Not yet.

251
00:15:21,935 --> 00:15:24,403
You got yourself in quite
a predicament, Mr. Crewe.

252
00:15:24,604 --> 00:15:27,072
- Is that right?
- See, it's just come to my attention

253
00:15:27,274 --> 00:15:29,333
that inmate Unger
has been taken into custody

254
00:15:29,543 --> 00:15:31,010
for the murder of Caretaker.

255
00:15:31,211 --> 00:15:33,577
- Good.
- Oh, yeah, it's good.

256
00:15:34,047 --> 00:15:37,414
Only thing is, he claims
to have an accomplice.

257
00:15:37,851 --> 00:15:39,614
Claims you knew all about it.

258
00:15:39,820 --> 00:15:43,017
Hell, he even says
you sent Caretaker to your cell.

259
00:15:44,157 --> 00:15:45,385
Bullshit.

260
00:15:45,592 --> 00:15:48,789
Captain Knauer says
he saw you planning it with Unger.

261
00:15:50,197 --> 00:15:51,892
There's no way
that could hold up in court.

262
00:15:52,099 --> 00:15:53,088
Court?

263
00:15:54,968 --> 00:15:59,337
Hell, boy, in Allenville,
I'm the judge, I'm the jury,

264
00:15:59,539 --> 00:16:03,703
and in your particular case,
I'm the executioner.

265
00:16:04,578 --> 00:16:05,602
What do you want?

266
00:16:06,146 --> 00:16:07,773
I want you to lose.

267
00:16:07,981 --> 00:16:09,141
I can't do that.

268
00:16:09,349 --> 00:16:12,341
Of course you can. After all,
you've had plenty of practice.

269
00:16:12,552 --> 00:16:15,988
But the men. It's more important
to them than it is to you.

270
00:16:17,224 --> 00:16:19,283
Okay. Suit yourself.

271
00:16:19,659 --> 00:16:23,095
Spend the next 25 years
of your useless life in prison.

272
00:16:25,332 --> 00:16:27,061
All right, I'll do it.

273
00:16:31,071 --> 00:16:34,905
But I don't want my guys hurt.
You get ahead, you coast. We clear?

274
00:16:35,108 --> 00:16:37,804
Fine. Right after I get
a two-touchdown lead.

275
00:16:39,379 --> 00:16:42,143
I tell you what bothers me
the most, warden.

276
00:16:44,317 --> 00:16:47,081
That you're not gonna be
out there on that field with us,

277
00:16:47,287 --> 00:16:49,118
getting what you got coming to you.

278
00:16:52,225 --> 00:16:55,058
The only thing coming to me
is victory.

279
00:16:57,230 --> 00:16:58,663
Mean Machine.

280
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:01,495
It's cute.

281
00:17:04,671 --> 00:17:06,400
- Let's go, boy!
- We can do it, baby!

282
00:17:06,606 --> 00:17:08,096
Captain.

283
00:17:09,042 --> 00:17:10,441
May I have a word?

284
00:17:10,644 --> 00:17:13,135
Don't worry, warden,
we'll take care of business.

285
00:17:13,346 --> 00:17:14,472
I already have.

286
00:17:14,915 --> 00:17:17,543
What? We can win this on our own.

287
00:17:17,751 --> 00:17:21,812
Captain, a man in my position
doesn't leave things to chance.

288
00:17:22,556 --> 00:17:25,684
Now, after you get a comfortable
three-touchdown lead,

289
00:17:25,892 --> 00:17:28,725
I want you to inflict as much pain
as humanly possible.

290
00:17:28,929 --> 00:17:31,124
Do not let up, you hear?

291
00:17:31,498 --> 00:17:34,399
I want those cons to understand
who owns them.

292
00:17:35,268 --> 00:17:36,565
Do I make myself clear?

293
00:17:36,770 --> 00:17:38,067
Oh, yes, sir.

294
00:17:38,872 --> 00:17:39,839
Good.

295
00:17:40,740 --> 00:17:44,232
<i>There's the kickoff, and we're
under way in the second half.</i>

296
00:17:49,983 --> 00:17:53,077
<i>Megget is finally brought down
at the guards' 33,</i>

297
00:17:53,286 --> 00:17:54,878
<i>where Paul Crewe will take over.</i>

298
00:17:55,088 --> 00:17:56,885
<i>And what a first half he's had.</i>

299
00:17:57,090 --> 00:17:58,352
Here we go! Here we go!

300
00:18:01,528 --> 00:18:02,825
Down, set!

301
00:18:03,597 --> 00:18:05,724
Y 45. Hut!

302
00:18:06,633 --> 00:18:09,101
<i>On first and 10, Crewe will pass.</i>

303
00:18:09,302 --> 00:18:10,997
<i>- He's got Deacon wide open.
- Come on.</i>

304
00:18:11,204 --> 00:18:12,364
<i>Oh, incomplete.</i>

305
00:18:12,572 --> 00:18:13,664
It's okay. Get your head up.

306
00:18:14,241 --> 00:18:15,208
It's all right, man.

307
00:18:17,210 --> 00:18:18,438
Come on, Paulie.

308
00:18:18,645 --> 00:18:21,910
<i>Second and 10 from the 33. Crewe's
looking for Deacon once again.</i>

309
00:18:22,115 --> 00:18:24,276
- He's open!
- He's open!

310
00:18:24,951 --> 00:18:28,853
<i>But overthrows it.
And it's picked off by Papajohn.</i>

311
00:18:29,055 --> 00:18:30,579
<i>Look out! He might go.</i>

312
00:18:32,192 --> 00:18:33,853
<i>Say goodbye.</i>

313
00:18:34,628 --> 00:18:35,617
<i>Touchdown!</i>

314
00:18:37,697 --> 00:18:41,258
The first mistake
Crewe's made all day.

315
00:18:44,304 --> 00:18:48,035
Short memory, baby.
We'll get it back. We'll get it back.

316
00:18:48,241 --> 00:18:49,868
Defense, let's do this!

317
00:18:51,077 --> 00:18:52,669
<i>8:38 left in the third quarter,</i>

318
00:18:52,879 --> 00:18:54,870
<i>and Crewe has struggled
thus far in the second half.</i>

319
00:18:55,081 --> 00:18:56,514
Hut!

320
00:18:56,716 --> 00:19:00,152
<i>The pitch to Megget.
Oh, my! That ball is live!</i>

321
00:19:01,187 --> 00:19:02,779
<i>It's picked up by Lambert.</i>

322
00:19:02,989 --> 00:19:06,254
<i>He's at the 15, the 10,
and he will score!</i>

323
00:19:07,961 --> 00:19:09,724
Yeah! Touchdown! Yeah!

324
00:19:09,930 --> 00:19:14,128
<i>Crewe took a shot on that play
and he's getting up slowly.</i>

325
00:19:14,334 --> 00:19:17,770
<i>Meanwhile, in the end zone, the guards
have something to celebrate,</i>

326
00:19:17,971 --> 00:19:20,462
<i>as they find themselves up
by two touchdowns.</i>

327
00:19:20,674 --> 00:19:24,235
<i>This is simply a different Paul Crewe
we're seeing here in the second half.</i>

328
00:19:24,444 --> 00:19:26,935
There's the old Paul Crewe
we love to write about.

329
00:19:27,147 --> 00:19:28,876
What the hell are you
doing out there?

330
00:19:29,082 --> 00:19:30,572
I'm done.

331
00:19:31,885 --> 00:19:33,352
I'm out. That's it.

332
00:19:35,755 --> 00:19:37,518
- Where you hurting?
- My knee.

333
00:19:37,724 --> 00:19:39,749
- Seems okay to me.
- Well, it ain't.

334
00:19:42,429 --> 00:19:46,263
If Crewe can't go, I don't know how
deep these guys are at quarterback.

335
00:19:48,335 --> 00:19:51,771
<i>The guards will try to keep it away
from Megget, so they'll pooch kick.</i>

336
00:19:51,972 --> 00:19:53,234
Fair catch. Fair catch.

337
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:56,034
<i>As Big Tony calls for the fair catch.</i>

338
00:19:56,509 --> 00:20:00,172
<i>Watch out. That was as late a hit
as I've ever seen.</i>

339
00:20:01,948 --> 00:20:05,748
<i>And even some of the home crowd
not liking that one.</i>

340
00:20:05,952 --> 00:20:07,010
Hang in there, partner.

341
00:20:07,220 --> 00:20:11,213
Can of corn. Can of corn,
and I'll be fine. Can of corn.

342
00:20:14,327 --> 00:20:16,522
Yeah, I'd have a hard time
looking at me too.

343
00:20:17,097 --> 00:20:18,223
Brucie.

344
00:20:18,431 --> 00:20:19,523
Yeah, coach.

345
00:20:19,733 --> 00:20:23,191
You're the only one that knows
this offense, son. Now, do it.

346
00:20:23,403 --> 00:20:25,769
<i>Coming into the game,
replacing the injured Paul Crewe,</i>

347
00:20:25,972 --> 00:20:27,303
<i>is number 1, Brucie.</i>

348
00:20:27,507 --> 00:20:29,338
All right, all right.
Crewe's playing like shit.

349
00:20:29,542 --> 00:20:31,635
That's his problem.
I'm gonna bring us back.

350
00:20:31,845 --> 00:20:34,211
Right, 32 Flex Dive Motion
on one. Ready!

351
00:20:34,414 --> 00:20:35,381
Break!

352
00:20:35,582 --> 00:20:38,176
Yeah. It's Brucie's
time to shine, baby.

353
00:20:38,752 --> 00:20:41,243
Okay. Down, set. Hut!

354
00:20:41,454 --> 00:20:45,356
<i>There's the snap and the ball is
fumbled. And the guards recover.</i>

355
00:20:45,558 --> 00:20:47,253
I knew I shouldn't
have had that popcorn.

356
00:20:48,428 --> 00:20:52,194
The guards are in command here
as we move late into the third quarter.

357
00:20:52,399 --> 00:20:53,764
Ninety-eight. Hut! Hut!

358
00:20:54,768 --> 00:20:57,794
<i>The give is to Potter.
Back to Knauer.</i>

359
00:20:58,004 --> 00:21:00,268
<i>He's got a man open
deep downfield.</i>

360
00:21:00,473 --> 00:21:02,407
<i>He'll throw the flea-flicker!</i>

361
00:21:02,609 --> 00:21:05,271
<i>And he's got it. Touchdown, guards.</i>

362
00:21:05,478 --> 00:21:08,538
<i>And this game is starting
to look like a blowout.</i>

363
00:21:10,617 --> 00:21:14,713
Hey, man, after all Caretaker did,
this is how you show him love?

364
00:21:14,921 --> 00:21:16,286
Don't worry about it.

365
00:21:16,489 --> 00:21:18,753
You haven't changed one damn bit.

366
00:21:23,229 --> 00:21:24,958
All right. Down, set!

367
00:21:25,165 --> 00:21:26,393
<i>Back in at quarterback is Brucie,</i>

368
00:21:26,599 --> 00:21:29,432
<i>who will try to find a handle
on the ball this time.</i>

369
00:21:30,603 --> 00:21:31,865
Throw it, Brucie!

370
00:21:32,405 --> 00:21:33,872
Oh, shit!

371
00:21:34,207 --> 00:21:35,606
<i>And look out.</i>

372
00:21:39,646 --> 00:21:41,705
<i>What a shot he took!</i>

373
00:21:42,015 --> 00:21:43,380
How much more blood do you want?

374
00:21:46,553 --> 00:21:50,250
<i>I think the cons are just about
out of options at quarterback.</i>

375
00:22:09,642 --> 00:22:11,769
Hey, Skitchy,
let me ask you something.

376
00:22:12,679 --> 00:22:15,580
When you popped the warden,
was it worth it?

377
00:22:15,782 --> 00:22:17,909
Was it worth spending
the rest of your life in here?

378
00:22:18,618 --> 00:22:22,452
Was it worth it? It was worth
every goddamn second.

379
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:32,227
What the hell is he doing?

380
00:22:35,135 --> 00:22:38,764
Paul Crewe must be feeling better,
because here he comes.

381
00:22:38,972 --> 00:22:41,338
All right, I missed you guys,
so I'm back.

382
00:22:41,541 --> 00:22:43,805
We got a lot of work to do.
Let's get it going.

383
00:22:44,010 --> 00:22:46,604
Deuce right, 89. Fly on two. Ready?

384
00:22:48,948 --> 00:22:50,006
Break.

385
00:22:51,584 --> 00:22:54,610
<i>As we start the fourth quarter,
cons down by three touchdowns.</i>

386
00:22:54,821 --> 00:22:56,118
Wide left! Tight left!

387
00:22:57,857 --> 00:22:59,882
Black 90. Hut! Hut!

388
00:23:00,093 --> 00:23:02,653
<i>Here comes the blitz,
and no one's blocking!</i>

389
00:23:02,862 --> 00:23:05,854
<i>And Crewe will be sacked
for a big loss.</i>

390
00:23:06,533 --> 00:23:10,560
<i>That looked like a message to Crewe
from his offensive line.</i>

391
00:23:12,238 --> 00:23:13,967
Did you see that, man?
They're quitting on him.

392
00:23:14,174 --> 00:23:16,165
Okay, baby. Jailbreak Blitz. Ready?

393
00:23:16,509 --> 00:23:18,636
We got that out of the way.
I deserved it.

394
00:23:18,845 --> 00:23:21,211
- Now we gotta play some football.
- Switch it! Switch it!

395
00:23:21,414 --> 00:23:23,507
<i>Cons need to do something
to get back in this game.</i>

396
00:23:23,716 --> 00:23:25,547
<i>And that's not it!</i>

397
00:23:26,352 --> 00:23:28,343
<i>And Crewe is leveled!</i>

398
00:23:28,555 --> 00:23:30,853
I don't think he's gonna get up
from that one.

399
00:23:31,057 --> 00:23:32,524
Nice hit!

400
00:23:34,427 --> 00:23:37,021
<i>But he is. And I don't know how,
after that last hit.</i>

401
00:23:37,230 --> 00:23:38,356
All right, punt team!

402
00:23:38,565 --> 00:23:40,931
Keep them off the field!
We're going for it.

403
00:23:41,134 --> 00:23:42,999
Dumbshits are going for it!
Let's go! Let's go!

404
00:23:43,369 --> 00:23:46,304
Come on back, if he wants to get
his ass kicked. Come on back.

405
00:23:46,506 --> 00:23:47,768
<i>This is unbelievable.</i>

406
00:23:47,974 --> 00:23:52,138
Fine. You guys don't wanna help me,
I'll do it on my own. On two.

407
00:23:53,146 --> 00:23:54,374
Let's go, to the line.

408
00:23:54,581 --> 00:23:55,912
<i>On fourth and 20,</i>

409
00:23:56,115 --> 00:23:58,913
<i>the cons are gonna go for it.
This could be the ball game right here.</i>

410
00:23:59,118 --> 00:24:01,177
Red 98. Hut! Hut!

411
00:24:02,789 --> 00:24:06,486
<i>Crewe dodges the blitz,
but he loses his helmet.</i>

412
00:24:09,963 --> 00:24:11,487
<i>And he's not going down.</i>

413
00:24:17,103 --> 00:24:19,367
<i>He's got the first down.</i>

414
00:24:19,572 --> 00:24:20,800
Time-out!

415
00:24:21,507 --> 00:24:23,168
- Man, oh, man.
- Not bad.

416
00:24:30,750 --> 00:24:31,978
Huddle up.

417
00:24:33,086 --> 00:24:34,075
Look.

418
00:24:35,188 --> 00:24:38,646
I'm sure you already know this,
but I never said it out loud.

419
00:24:40,126 --> 00:24:41,889
I did throw that game.

420
00:24:43,329 --> 00:24:44,626
I did it.

421
00:24:45,465 --> 00:24:48,298
I was in a bad way
with some worse people.

422
00:24:49,135 --> 00:24:50,466
After I did it,

423
00:24:50,670 --> 00:24:54,697
I felt so shitty I wish I would have
just let them kill me instead.

424
00:24:55,375 --> 00:24:59,744
Now the warden wants to pin
Caretaker's murder on me

425
00:24:59,946 --> 00:25:01,880
if I don't throw this game.

426
00:25:03,716 --> 00:25:06,184
So it looks like I'm gonna get
to know you guys a lot better,

427
00:25:06,386 --> 00:25:09,014
because I ain't doing that
twice in a lifetime.

428
00:25:09,222 --> 00:25:12,419
We got a little time left.
We can still do this.

429
00:25:12,625 --> 00:25:15,719
I'm begging you.
Put your hands in here.

430
00:25:25,471 --> 00:25:28,531
Okay. Thank you. Now, who are we?

431
00:25:28,741 --> 00:25:29,765
Mean Machine!

432
00:25:29,976 --> 00:25:32,342
Come on, Mean Machine, let's go!

433
00:25:35,682 --> 00:25:36,944
That's great news.

434
00:25:37,150 --> 00:25:39,914
All right. We got ourselves a game.

435
00:25:40,119 --> 00:25:41,711
Brown 65. Hut!

436
00:25:41,921 --> 00:25:45,982
<i>First and 10 from the 30.
Crewe finds Deacon open in the flat.</i>

437
00:25:48,094 --> 00:25:49,061
Hut!

438
00:25:50,763 --> 00:25:53,630
<i>The give is to Megget. And he fights
his way for a 9-yard gain.</i>

439
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:55,528
One yard, baby. One more yard.

440
00:25:56,936 --> 00:25:57,960
Hut! Hut!

441
00:25:58,171 --> 00:26:00,162
<i>Crewe tries a sneak. Or is it?</i>

442
00:26:00,373 --> 00:26:01,840
<i>He flips it back to Megget.</i>

443
00:26:02,342 --> 00:26:05,368
<i>Megget's got the first down
and more.</i>

444
00:26:12,752 --> 00:26:16,711
<i>And Megget is down to the 4-yard
line, where it'll be first and goal.</i>

445
00:26:16,923 --> 00:26:18,015
Hut!

446
00:26:19,058 --> 00:26:22,687
<i>Crewe hands it to Turley.
And look at the big man go.</i>

447
00:26:22,895 --> 00:26:24,123
Tackle him!

448
00:26:29,869 --> 00:26:30,927
<i>Touchdown!</i>

449
00:26:32,038 --> 00:26:36,270
That was some rumbling, bumbling
stumbling right there.

450
00:26:36,476 --> 00:26:38,239
<i>And listen to the crowd</i>

451
00:26:38,444 --> 00:26:42,107
<i>as this underdog con team
